INSERT INTO public.topic_contents (id, topic_id, content_index, content, created_at) VALUES (5475, 6426, 0, e'Indian Astrology, or Jyoti·π£a (meaning the \'science of light\'), is a complex, ancient discipline that fundamentally differs from Western astrology in its approach and calculations. Categorized under both philosophy and divination, it forms a central pillar of traditional Hindu life.
INSERT INTO public.topic_contents (id, topic_id, content_index, content, created_at) VALUES (5476, 6427, 0, e'Ancient Philosophy, originating in the 6th century BCE, marks a pivotal intellectual transition: the shift from *mythos* (stories of the gods) to *logos* (rational explanation). It was a quest for ultimate reality and the meaning of existence, essentially serving as humanity‚Äôs first systematic spiritual pursuit divorced from priestly authority.
INSERT INTO public.topic_contents (id, topic_id, content_index, content, created_at) VALUES (5477, 6428, 0, e'**Ancient India: The Foundation of Dharma and Cosmic Order**
INSERT INTO public.topic_contents (id, topic_id, content_index, content, created_at) VALUES (5478, 6429, 0, e'The Ramayana, meaning "Rama‚Äôs Journey," is one of the world‚Äôs most significant ancient epics (*Mahakavyas*). Attributed to the sage Valmiki, this foundational text of Hindu spirituality chronicles the life and trials of Prince Rama, the seventh avatar of the god Vishnu and the embodiment of perfect righteousness (*Dharma*).
INSERT INTO public.topic_contents (id, topic_id, content_index, content, created_at) VALUES (5479, 6430, 0, e'The **Mahabharata** is one of the two major Sanskrit epics of ancient India (the other being the *Ramayana*). Far exceeding the length of the *Iliad* and *Odyssey* combined, it is an unparalleled treasure trove of Hindu mythology, philosophy, and spirituality.
